  "market_context": "Daily chart showed a bearish close after sweeping the prior daily high. Analyst dropped to hourly to identify a breaker block formed after a high sweep, then entered short on retest targeting prior lows.",
  "key_observation": "A daily high was swept with a bearish closure, establishing bearish bias; on hourly, a swing high sweep created a bearish breaker block (high-low-higher high-lower low), enabling a continuation short entry.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: On the daily chart, observed a sweep of the prior daily high followed by a bearish candle close, confirming bearish daily structure and bias.",
    "Step 2: Dropped to the hourly chart and identified a sweep of a recent swing high, forming a sequence: high → low → higher high → lower low, defining a bearish breaker block.",
    "Step 3: Marked the breaker block (the series of candles between the initial high and the lower low) as the POI for entry.",
    "Step 4: Waited for price to retest the breaker block zone, placed stop above the breaker’s high (other side of the breaker), and targeted previous swing lows for a 2R reward.",
    "Step 5: Entry executed on retest; price moved lower and hit the 2R target as projected."
  ],
  "outcome": "Trade hit 2R target successfully.",
  "lessons": "A daily high sweep with bearish closure sets bias; on lower time frames, a breaker block formed after a high sweep provides high-probability continuation entries when retested, especially with tight stops and 2R targets.",
